tldr: The agent reviewed the sleep questionnaire application against the
  provided specification and implemented several missing features. Key additions
  include a tiredness severity scale, COMISA detection, insufficient sleep
  syndrome detection, outbound resource links, weighted EDS scoring, full CSV
  export, and chronic fatigue/pain screening.
overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, providing a detailed specification. The agent performed an
  in-depth analysis, identifying several critical and medium-priority missing
  features. Subsequently, the agent systematically implemented these features.
  This included adding a 1-10 severity scale for tiredness with safety
  messaging, implementing detection and recommendations for COMISA and
  Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, integrating a dedicated resources section with
  outbound links in both the web and PDF reports, and refining the Excessive
  Daytime Sleepiness (EDS) scoring with weighted calculations. Furthermore, the
  CSV export functionality was expanded to include all questionnaire data, and
  new questions for pain severity and chronic fatigue screening were added,
  complete with corresponding report logic. The implementation ensured
  consistency across data models, validation, and user interface components.
